From d0232053a62ff1bd1b1be6b2e5bc3cc335a6cc2a Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Zach Taylor <zctaylor.work@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 21 May 2026 11:56:44 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 19/48] Add warp.terminal command-lifecycle events (oh-my-warp)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Plugins react to shell commands via warp.terminal.onCommandStart /
onCommandFinished. Callbacks are registered through RegisterEventHandlerService
into a per-event registry (app/src/plugin/events.rs); the terminal view fires
them from the AfterBlockStarted/AfterBlockCompleted handlers with a
{command, exitCode, cwd, durationMs} payload via CallJsFunctionService. A
callback that returns a string shows it as a toast (lenient OptionalToast,
shown at the ctx-rich fire site — no host→app hop). See PLUGIN_SPEC.md (M2).
